OL,3,CInquest finds no fault in medical care
OL,4,Cafter 17-year-old's death in Jersey.
OL,6,FAfter the inquest concluded, Jersey's
OL,7,FMedical Director Simon West said: "I'd
OL,8,Flike to send my sincere condolences to
OL,9,FDaisy Stephenson's family and my
OL,10,Fthoughts remain with them during what
OL,11,FI know has been an incredibly
OL,12,Fdifficult time.
OL,14,F"The inquest confirmed that the care
OL,15,Fprovided by Health and Care Jersey met
OL,16,Fthe appropriate standards expected. We
OL,17,Falways reflect after every inquest and
OL,18,Fremain committed to continually
OL,19,Fenhancing our services and ensuring
OL,20,Fthe highest standards of care for all
OL,21,Four patients.
